title: A Bunch of Everlastings; or, Texts that made History
creator: Frank W. Boreham
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of A Bunch of Everlastings; or, Texts that made History, by Frank W. Boreham. Read by Tim Bower. A collection of brief biographies and the text from scripture that was significant in the life of each. It is biography and devotional Bible study expertly woven together to produce interesting and inspirational stories. (Summary by Tim Bower) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
